0 -20 Td
(Effective Date: January 15, 2024) Tj
0 -40 Td
(1. PURPOSE AND SCOPE) Tj
0 -20 Td
(This Standard Operating Procedure establishes the design controls) Tj
0 -20 Td
(process for medical device development in accordance with FDA) Tj
0 -20 Td
(21 CFR 820.30 and ISO 13485 requirements.) Tj
0 -40 Td
(2. DESIGN AND DEVELOPMENT PLANNING) Tj
0 -20 Td
(2.1 Design planning shall be documented and shall identify:) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Design and development activities) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Personnel responsible for each design activity) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Verification and validation requirements) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Design transfer criteria) Tj
0 -40 Td
(3. DESIGN INPUTS) Tj
0 -20 Td
(3.1 Design inputs shall be documented and shall include:) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Intended use and indications for use) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- User needs and user requirements) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Functional requirements and performance requirements) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Safety requirements including risk analysis) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Applicable statutory and regulatory requirements) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Applicable standards and guidance documents) Tj
0 -40 Td
(4. DESIGN OUTPUTS) Tj
0 -20 Td
(4.1 Design outputs shall be documented and shall:) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Meet the design input requirements) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Contain specifications for purchasing, production, and servicing) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Define acceptance criteria for the device) Tj
0 -20 Td
(- Identify characteristics critical to device safety and performance) Tj
0 -40 Td
(5. DESIGN REVIEW) Tj
0 -20 Td
(5.1 Design reviews shall be conducted at appropriate stages) Tj
0 -20 Td
(to evaluate design adequacy and identify design problems.) Tj
0 -20 Td
(Design review participants shall include representatives) Tj
0 -20 Td
(from functions concerned with the design stage being reviewed.) Tj
0 -40 Td
(6. DESIGN VERIFICATION) Tj
0 -20 Td
(6.1 Design verification shall confirm that design outputs) Tj
0 -20 Td
(meet design input requirements through objective evidence.) Tj
0 -20 Td
(Verification activities may include design calculations,) Tj
0 -20 Td
(similarity analyses, bench testing, and clinical studies.) Tj
0 -40 Td
(7. DESIGN VALIDATION) Tj
0 -20 Td
(7.1 Design validation shall demonstrate that devices) Tj
0 -20 Td
(conform to user needs and intended uses under actual) Tj
0 -20 Td
(or simulated use conditions. Clinical evaluation may) Tj
0 -20 Td
(be part of design validation activities.) Tj
0 -40 Td
(8. DESIGN TRANSFER) Tj
0 -20 Td
(8.1 Design transfer activities shall ensure that) Tj
0 -20 Td
(the device design is correctly translated into) Tj
0 -20 Td
(production specifications and procedures.) Tj
0 -40 Td
(9. DESIGN CHANGES) Tj
0 -20 Td
(9.1 Design changes shall be identified, documented,) Tj
0 -20 Td
(validated, verified as appropriate, reviewed, and approved) Tj
0 -20 Td
(before implementation in accordance with change control procedures.) Tj
0 -40 Td
(10. DESIGN HISTORY FILE) Tj
0 -20 Td
(10.1 A design history file shall be maintained for each) Tj
0 -20 Td
(device type containing records of design control activities.) Tj
